03/06/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Police on Wednesday (June 2nd) arrested the former director of Serbian Railways, Milanko Sarancic, for suspected abuse of office, along with three other former officials. Sarancic was arrested over a 2004 deal to buy six diesel engines from Slovenia and Sweden, resulting in damages to the company's budget totalling 1.2m euros. (Tanjug, Beta, B92, RTS - 02/06/10)
